<%= render "shared/teacher_mailer/reference_number" %>

Dear <%= application_form_full_name(@application_form) %>,

A senior Professional Recognition Manager has reviewed your decision review request, including the evidence and reasons you provided.

<% if @decision_review_request.review_passed %>
They found that your application meets the eligibility criteria. This means the decline decision has been removed.

Your application will now move to the next stage of the assessment process.

If the assessment team needs more information before making a final decision, they will contact you by email.
<% else %>
They found that your application does not meet the eligibility criteria. This means the decline decision has not changed.

Note from the senior Professional Recognition Manager:

<%= @decision_review_request.review_note %>

## What you can do next

You’ll be able to make a new application once you’ve addressed all decline reasons given. If you reapply for QTS, you’ll not be able to review the details of your previous application.

You may want to explore [other routes to getting QTS](https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/apply-for-qualified-teacher-status-qts-if-you-teach-outside-the-uk/routes-to-qualified-teacher-status-qts-for-teachers-and-those-with-teaching-experience-outside-the-uk#routes-to-qts).

If you disagree with the outcome of this decision review, you are entitled to submit a final appeal to a senior Professional Recognition Manager. To make an appeal request, email [<%= t("service.email.enquiries") %>](mailto:<%= t("service.email.enquiries") %>). You will need to provide additional evidence to show:

* an error in law has occurred
* a factual error has occurred in the application of the law
* the Professional Recognition due process has not been applied in assessing your application
* show you meet the eligibility criteria for QTS in England
<% end %>

